    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">How much do solar panels cost in Ohio?</h3>
    <p>Solar panel costs in Ohio typically range from \$2.50 to \$3.50 per watt installed, before incentives. For a typical 8kW residential system, homeowners can expect to pay between \$20,000 and \$24,700 before the federal tax credit. After applying the 30% federal Investment Tax Credit, the net cost ranges from \$14,000 to \$17,290. Additional savings come from Ohio's property tax exemption and sales tax exemption on solar equipment. Most Ohio solar installations pay for themselves within 10-14 years through electricity savings, after which they continue generating free electricity for the remainder of their 25-year warranty period.</p>
  </div>
  
