    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">What SEER rating is recommended for Ohio?</h3>
    <p>For Ohio's climate, SEER ratings of 16-18 provide the best balance of efficiency and cost-effectiveness for most homes. While the minimum SEER requirement is 14, higher efficiency systems perform better in Ohio's humid summers and qualify for utility rebates and federal tax credits. Variable-speed systems with SEER ratings of 18-20 excel in humidity control, which is particularly important during Ohio's muggy summer months. For heat pumps, look for HSPF2 ratings of 8.5 or higher to ensure efficient heating performance during Ohio's cold winters.</p>
  </div>
  
